summary: On November 2, 2024, the Tennessee Volunteers defeated the Kentucky Wildcats in a thrilling college football game at Kroger Field in Lexington, Kentucky. The final score was 45-31, with Tennessee scoring the winning touchdown with just over a minute remaining in the game. The victory kept Tennessee in contention for a spot in the College Football Playoff. The game was nationally televised on SEC Network and drew a large online audience, with many fans streaming the game live. Tennessee's victory was fueled by a strong performance from quarterback Hendon Hooker, who threw for over 300 yards and three touchdowns. Running back Jabari Small also had a big game for the Vols, rushing for over 100 yards and two touchdowns. Kentucky was led by quarterback Will Levis, who threw for over 250 yards and two touchdowns. Running back Chris Rodriguez also had a solid performance for the Wildcats, rushing for over 100 yards and a touchdown. The game was a back-and-forth affair, with both teams trading blows throughout the contest. In the end, however, Tennessee was able to make the decisive plays in the fourth quarter to secure the victory.
